title: Running Route To Ceres Woods
name: Running Route To Ceres Woods
description: This is one of my primary running routes.

properties.name: Starting Point
properties.description: This is a good starting point, there is plenty of parking and most of the times the restrooms attached to the team house are open.

properties.name: Path to Ceres Woods Part 1
properties.description: This my typical route to Ceres Woods. This part is on roads mostly through a neighborhood so I might try a different side street to mix it up from time to time.

properties.name: Path to Ceres Woods
properties.description: This is the path out to Ceres Woods. It's a mix of roads and trails.

properties.name: Ceres Woods Lambs Rd Entrance
properties.description: This is the Lambs Rd entrance to the wood. Note there really isn't a park lot, it's just a cut out into the woods.

properties.name: Ceres Woods
properties.description: This is the Ceres Woods, it is split into a few different properties between the township and county. Since the tree coverage is thick it is not possible to map the trails but there are many miles of trails

properties.name: Ceres Woods Pitman Rd Parking lot
properties.description: This is a fairly large parking lot set into the woods a couple hundred feet, giving the park an alternative entrance.

properties.name: Placemark 4
properties.description: This is another entrance, with a parking lot. I usually use this as my exit for my loop.

properties.name: Route back
properties.description: The path back is all roads, changing to sidewalks in downtown Pitman but is scenic and comfortable.

properties.name: Main Trail
properties.description: This trail is the quickest path through the woods. It is very wide and easy to follow. There are plenty of side trails that split off but they are much narrow. The path wines more then it appears on the map.
